Peter Dickson Kinder of Missouri has been appointed as the Alternate Federal Co-Chairperson of the Delta Regional Authority. He has served as the Lt. Governor of Missouri since 2004 and was the only Republican to win statewide office in both 2008 and 2012. Kinder has also served as the acting Governor of Missouri for 105 days. Before his role as Lt. Governor, Kinder served three terms in the Missouri Senate from 1993 to 2005, where he led his party to the majority in 2001. He has also worked on Capitol Hill, served as a real estate attorney, and worked in newspaper publishing. Kinder currently serves on the board of the Southeast Missouri Regional Port Authority. He is a native of Southeast Missouri and was admitted to the Missouri Bar in 1980. Kinder holds a bachelor's degree from Southeast Missouri State University and a J.D. from St. Mary's University.